{"word":"Cedron","slug":"cedron","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>Cedron</b> Called also Kidron.<br/> Brook of, running south under the eastern wall of Jerusalem<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=11&chapter=2&verse=37'>1Ki 2:37</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=16&chapter=2&verse=15'>Neh 2:15</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=24&chapter=31&verse=40'>Jer 31:40</a><br/> Idols destroyed on the banks of:<br/> - By Asa<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=11&chapter=15&verse=13'>1Ki 15:13</a> <br/> - By Josiah<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=23&verse=6'>2Ki 23:6</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=23&verse=12'>2Ki 23:12</a> <br/> - By Hezekiah<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=14&chapter=29&verse=16'>2Ch 29:16</a> <br/> Its channel changed by Hezekiah<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=14&chapter=32&verse=4'>2Ch 32:4</a>"}]}